title: Ecclesiastes (KJV)
creator: King James Version
description: LibriVox recording of Ecclesiastes, from The King James Version. The Book of Ecclesiastes is a wonderful book. It tells how all man's doing is futile, if it is done in his own strength. The last two verses sum it up quite nicely: "Let us hear the conclusion of the whole matter: Fear God, and keep his commandments: for this is the whole duty of man. For God shall bring every work into judgment, with every secret thing, whether it be good, or whether it be evil. (Summary by GabrielleC) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (16MB)
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; ancient texts; religion
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
